-- California Businesswoman to Plead Guilty in Israeli Banks Case
-- B y   D a v i d   V o r e a c o s
-- 2013-04-12T19:57:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-12/california-businesswoman-to-plead-guilty-in-israeli-banks-case.html
A California businesswoman agreed
to plead guilty to conspiring to use accounts at two Israeli
banks to hide as much as $2.5 million from the  Internal Revenue
Service , according to the U.S. Justice Department.  Guity Kashfi was charged today in federal court in the
Central District of California, where prosecutors filed a plea
agreement that she signed, the Justice Department said today in
a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Voreacos in Newark at 
